The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Sunday, February 22, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	The two-year ban on East Bengal coach Subhash Bhowmick is set to be reduced. The IFA authorities informed on Saturday that the ban could be something between six months to one year. The decision will be taken in the governing body meeting of the association on March 1.				 																																																	Meanwhile, the IFA has granted Rs 2 lakh to East Bengal for the hosting of the three AFC Cup home matches. 				 																																																	 Border Security Force (SB) and Hooghly District won the mens and womens titles in the 53rd state basketball championships held at the Dum Dum Central Jail ground. Dum Dum Vikas Sporting Club and Coal India Sports Promotion Board won the sub-junior and junior titles, respectively.				 																																																	FOOTBALL: National League  Mohun Bagan vs Mohammedan Sporting (Salt Lake Stadium, 2:30 pm)
